    "is_snapshot": false,
    "description": "ASIN-level daily Sales & Traffic (one row per store/marketplace/day/child_asin/sku). Sourced from Amazon Data Kiosk GraphQL `analytics_salesAndTraffic_2024_04_24` (salesAndTrafficByAsin, CHILD granularity) — NOT the legacy GET_SALES_AND_TRAFFIC_REPORT. Amazon's nested `Amount {amount, currencyCode}` objects are unwrapped: the numeric money columns hold `.amount`, and `currency_code` holds the single shared currency for the row. `unit_session_percentage` is the conversion-rate metric (units_ordered / sessions); `buy_box_percentage` is the buy-box (featured offer) win rate. Use for per-ASIN daily sales/traffic and conversion analysis.",
